      %h1 VirtualBox Files
      %p Once you have VirtualBox installed, there are two files that you need:
      %ul
        %li Virtual machine settings file (has a .vbox file extension)
        %li Virtual machine disk (has a .vmdk file extension)
      %p The operating system for our virtual machine is stored on the virtual machine disk, and the settings for our virtual machine (i.e. the virtual hardware) are stored in the machine settings file.
      %p The latest version of both files can be found below:

      %table.table.table-condensed.table-bordered
        %thead
          %tr
            %th Version
            %th Released
            %th Virtual machine settings
            %th Virtual machine disk 

        %tbody
          %tr.success
            %td lbscoding_v03 (current version)
            %td 22/04/2013
            %td 
              %a{:href => "https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B8wIfRgDWrMhVDdLWjVPdzRVa2M/edit?usp=sharing", :target => "_blank"} lbscoding_v03.vbox
            %td 
              %a{:href => "https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B8wIfRgDWrMhVGFPZkN5OENJZ0k/edit?usp=sharing", :target => "_blank"} box-disk03.vmdk

          %tr
