      %h2 Setting up VirtualBox
      %p Follow these steps to ensure you have VirtualBox setup correctly
      %br/
      %p 1. Download the latest version of the two required files (see above)
      %br/
      %p 2. Launch Finder (bottom left icon) – on Windows open an Explorer window:
      %br/
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s021.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p Finder Window will then appear
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s022.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 3. Go to the Home folder – on Windows this can be your “My Documents” folder:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s031.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 4. Create a New Folder called...
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s041.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p ... [VirtualBox VMs] – don’t use brackets, case is significant:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s042.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 5. Within [VirtualBox VMs] create another folder called...
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s051.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p ... [lbscoding_v03] (use the name corresponding to the latest version - these images just show [lbscoding] to remain current):
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s052.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 6. Drag the VirtualBox files you downloaded into [lbscoding]
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s061.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p Files are now in the right place:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s062.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 7. Launch VirtualBox:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s071.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 8. Add a new machine:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s081.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 9. Find the lbscoding.vbox file we just moved into [VirtualBox VMs]/[lbscoding]. Click Open:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s091.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 10. The virtual machine will be added. Click Start to start the virtual machine:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s101.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 11. You can ignore these warnings that appear. If you want you can select "Do not show this message again"
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s111.png.jpg"}/
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s112.png.jpg"}/
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s113.png.jpg"}/
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s114.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 12. If you get here, good work. Log in with username: lbs, password: lbscoding:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s121.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 13. You should then see something like this:
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s131.png.jpg"}/
      %br/
      %br/
      %p 14. To turn off your virtual machine, click the Power icon in the top right hand corner of the virtual machine and select "Shut down"
      %img{:border => "0", :src => "img/s141.png.jpg"}/


